            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1869-07-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1869-07-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="421" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d421">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Barlow</persName>,
                                    United States marshal, to Mr. <persName type="to">Fish</persName>, Secretary of State.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                    </placeName>,
                                    <date calendar="gregorian" when="1869-07-15">
                        <hi rend="italic">July</hi> 15, 1869</date>.</dateline>
                <p rend="flushleft">
                    <seg type="margin">103]</seg> *<hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>:</p>
                <p>Have sent more marines to Gardner’s Island. Troops not needed at
                                present. There will be no trouble in getting the men on Gardner’s
                                Island to disperse, I think. I shall act discreetly and make no
                                commotion.</p>
                <p>The cutters and tugs have done all I asked; but I wish to know that I
                                can depend on them.</p>
                <p>Grinnell has given me every assistance possible, but is away
                                to-day.</p>
                <p>We can find no trace of the William Forster. Perhaps she is to come
                                from some other port to take up men.</p>
                <p>All is quiet, apparently: but we are looking out.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>FRANCIS C. BARLOW.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
